<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FF87FFCDA7ADFC48FC41D974" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0755A263FF87FFCDA7ADFC48FEF0DFC0" blockId="30.[189,310,935,961]" box="[189,310,935,961]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<heading id="5C1D150FFF87FFCDA7ADFC48FEF0DFC0" bold="true" box="[189,310,935,961]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF87FFCDA7ADFC48FEF0DFC0" bold="true" box="[189,310,935,961]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF87FFCDA7ADFC35FB6DD893" blockId="30.[188,1398,986,1170]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Based on 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF87FFCDA628FC35FD9EDFF5" author="Teruel R. &amp; Coulis M." box="[312,600,986,1012]" firstAuthor="Teruel" journalOrPublisher="Ecologica Montenegrina" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="30 - 36" part="13" refId="ref154406" refString="Teruel R. &amp; Coulis M. 2017. First record of the genus Charinus Simon, 1892 from Martinique, Lesser Antilles, with description of a new species (Amblypygi: Charinidae). Ecologica Montenegrina 13: 30 - 36. https: // doi. org / 10.37828 / em. 2017.13.3" title="First record of the genus Charinus Simon, 1892 from Martinique, Lesser Antilles, with description of a new species (Amblypygi: Charinidae)" type="journal article" year="2017">Teruel &amp; Coulis (2017)</bibRefCitation>
, this species may be separated from other Caribbean and Central American 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF87FFCDA628FBEDFE63D81D" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[312,421,1026,1052]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF87FFCDA628FBEDFE63D81D" box="[312,421,1026,1052]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Charinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by means of the following combination of characters: median eyes reduced; lateral eyes well developed; pedipalp femur with three dorsal spines and three ventral spines; pedipalp patella with three dorsal spines and two ventral spines; pedipalp tarsus with two dorsal spines; tibia of leg I with 23 articles, tarsus I with 37 articles; leg IV basitibia with two or three pseudo-articles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF87FFCDA7ADFB52FC41D974" blockId="30.[189,1399,1213,1397]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF87FFCDA7ADFB52FE13D8D6" authorityName="Teruel &amp; Coulis" authorityYear="2017" box="[189,469,1213,1239]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinicensis">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF87FFCDA7ADFB52FE13D8D6" box="[189,469,1213,1239]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Charinus martinicensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles most Caribbean species of 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF87FFCDA4A4FB52FBE7D8D6" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[948,1057,1213,1239]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF87FFCDA4A4FB52FBE7D8D6" box="[948,1057,1213,1239]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Charinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and shares with 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF87FFCDA3EBFB51FAB6D8D6" baseAuthorityName="Quintero" baseAuthorityYear="1983" box="[1275,1392,1214,1240]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acosta">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF87FFCDA3EBFB51FAB6D8D6" box="[1275,1392,1214,1240]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C. acosta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF87FFCDA7ADFB0AFE86D8FE" authorityName="Moya-Guzman" authorityYear="2009" box="[189,320,1253,1279]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aguayoi">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF87FFCDA7ADFB0AFE86D8FE" box="[189,320,1253,1279]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C. aguayoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF87FFCDA65FFB0AFE0ED8FE" authorityName="Teruel &amp; Questel" authorityYear="2011" box="[335,456,1253,1279]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bruneti">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF87FFCDA65FFB0AFE0ED8FE" box="[335,456,1253,1279]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C. bruneti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF87FFCDA515FB0AFDB9D8FE" authority="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff, 2021" authorityName="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff" authorityYear="2021" box="[517,639,1253,1279]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miskito" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF87FFCDA515FB0AFDB9D8FE" box="[517,639,1253,1279]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C. miskito</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="2EADC30AFF87FFCDA596FB0AFD23D8FE" box="[646,741,1253,1279]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, the presence of median eyes, although also reduced in in 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF87FFCDA7CCFAE2FE93D927" authorityName="Teruel &amp; Questel" authorityYear="2011" box="[220,341,1292,1319]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bruneti">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF87FFCDA7CCFAE2FE93D927" box="[220,341,1292,1319]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C. bruneti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF87FFCDA680FAE2FD94D927" authorityName="Teruel &amp; Coulis" authorityYear="2017" box="[400,594,1293,1319]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinicensis">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF87FFCDA680FAE2FD94D927" box="[400,594,1293,1319]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C. martinicensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF87FFCDA572FAE3FCB3D927" authorityName="Teruel &amp; Coulis" authorityYear="2017" box="[610,885,1292,1318]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinicensis">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF87FFCDA572FAE3FCB3D927" box="[610,885,1292,1318]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Charinus martinicensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from these species in the number of articles on the tibia and tarsus of leg I. The basitibia of leg IV consists of two to three pseudo-articles, common to all Caribbean and some South American species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FF87FFCDA7ADFA4EFECEDA14" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="0755A263FF87FFCDA7ADFA4EFE82D9BA" blockId="30.[189,324,1441,1467]" box="[189,324,1441,1467]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<heading id="5C1D150FFF87FFCDA7ADFA4EFE82D9BA" bold="true" box="[189,324,1441,1467]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF87FFCDA7ADFA4EFE82D9BA" bold="true" box="[189,324,1441,1467]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF87FFCDA7ADFA3CFECEDA14" blockId="30.[188,1399,1491,1557]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Latin adjective derived from the name of the island on which the species was collected (
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF87FFCDA3A9FA3CFF3ADA14" author="Teruel R. &amp; Coulis M." firstAuthor="Teruel" journalOrPublisher="Ecologica Montenegrina" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="30 - 36" part="13" refId="ref154406" refString="Teruel R. &amp; Coulis M. 2017. First record of the genus Charinus Simon, 1892 from Martinique, Lesser Antilles, with description of a new species (Amblypygi: Charinidae). Ecologica Montenegrina 13: 30 - 36. https: // doi. org / 10.37828 / em. 2017.13.3" title="First record of the genus Charinus Simon, 1892 from Martinique, Lesser Antilles, with description of a new species (Amblypygi: Charinidae)" type="journal article" year="2017">Teruel &amp; Coulis 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
