<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FF86FFCCA7ADFE1EFC3EDEF2" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0755A263FF86FFCCA7ADFE1EFEE9DE0A" blockId="31.[189,303,497,523]" box="[189,303,497,523]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<heading id="5C1D150FFF86FFCCA7ADFE1EFEE9DE0A" bold="true" box="[189,303,497,523]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF86FFCCA7ADFE1EFEE9DE0A" bold="true" box="[189,303,497,523]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF86FFCCA7ADFDCEFC3EDEF2" blockId="31.[189,1401,545,755]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF86FFCCA7ADFDCEFE16DE3A" author="Teruel R. &amp; Coulis M." box="[189,464,545,571]" firstAuthor="Teruel" journalOrPublisher="Ecologica Montenegrina" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="30 - 36" part="13" refId="ref154406" refString="Teruel R. &amp; Coulis M. 2017. First record of the genus Charinus Simon, 1892 from Martinique, Lesser Antilles, with description of a new species (Amblypygi: Charinidae). Ecologica Montenegrina 13: 30 - 36. https: // doi. org / 10.37828 / em. 2017.13.3" title="First record of the genus Charinus Simon, 1892 from Martinique, Lesser Antilles, with description of a new species (Amblypygi: Charinidae)" type="journal article" year="2017">Teruel &amp; Coulis (2017</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 2c–d) mention that 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF86FFCCA5E8FDCEFBCBDE3A" authorityName="Teruel &amp; Coulis" authorityYear="2017" box="[760,1037,545,571]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinicensis">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF86FFCCA5E8FDCEFBCBDE3A" box="[760,1037,545,571]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Charinus martinicensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a fully developed median eyes, a statement contradicted by their figure. The median eyes and ocular tubercle are clearly reduced and, as mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF86FFCCA6DBFD85FCDFDE84" author="Teruel R. &amp; Coulis M." box="[459,793,618,645]" firstAuthor="Teruel" journalOrPublisher="Ecologica Montenegrina" page="33" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="30 - 36" part="13" refId="ref154406" refString="Teruel R. &amp; Coulis M. 2017. First record of the genus Charinus Simon, 1892 from Martinique, Lesser Antilles, with description of a new species (Amblypygi: Charinidae). Ecologica Montenegrina 13: 30 - 36. https: // doi. org / 10.37828 / em. 2017.13.3" title="First record of the genus Charinus Simon, 1892 from Martinique, Lesser Antilles, with description of a new species (Amblypygi: Charinidae)" type="journal article" year="2017">Teruel &amp; Coulis (2017: 33)</bibRefCitation>
are “located inside a deep oval depression of the tegument”, typical of charinids with reduced median eyes. Although only female specimens were studied, 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF86FFCCA630FD5BFDF7DECF" author="Teruel R. &amp; Coulis M." box="[288,561,692,718]" firstAuthor="Teruel" journalOrPublisher="Ecologica Montenegrina" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="30 - 36" part="13" refId="ref154406" refString="Teruel R. &amp; Coulis M. 2017. First record of the genus Charinus Simon, 1892 from Martinique, Lesser Antilles, with description of a new species (Amblypygi: Charinidae). Ecologica Montenegrina 13: 30 - 36. https: // doi. org / 10.37828 / em. 2017.13.3" title="First record of the genus Charinus Simon, 1892 from Martinique, Lesser Antilles, with description of a new species (Amblypygi: Charinidae)" type="journal article" year="2017">Teruel &amp; Coulis (2017)</bibRefCitation>
do not provide information regarding the shape of the female gonopod. Similarly, no information is provided about the trichobothria of leg IV.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
